{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:proverbs.19",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 19,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 19 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:3",
      "text": "The folly of a man spoils his ways: and he blames God in his heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:4",
      "text": "Wealth acquires many friends; but the poor is deserted even of the friend he has.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:5",
      "text": "A false witness shall not be unpunished, and he that accuses unjustly shall not escape.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:6",
      "text": "Many court the favour of kings; but every bad man becomes a reproach to another man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:7",
      "text": "Every one who hates his poor brother shall also be far from friendship. Good understanding will draw near to them that know it, and a sensible man will find it. He that does much harm perfects mischief; and he that uses provoking words shall not escape.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:8",
      "text": "He that procures wisdom loves himself; and he that keeps wisdom shall find good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:9",
      "text": "A false witness shall not be unpunished; and whosoever shall kindle mischief shall perish by it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:10",
      "text": "Delight does not suit a fool, nor is it seemly if a servant should begin to rule with haughtiness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:11",
      "text": "A merciful man is long-suffering; and his triumph overtakes transgressors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:12",
      "text": "The threatening of a king is like the roaring of a lion; but as dew on the grass, so is his favour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:13",
      "text": "A foolish son is a disgrace to his father: vows paid out of the hire of a harlot are not pure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:14",
      "text": "Fathers divide house and substance to their children: but a wife is suited to a man by the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:15",
      "text": "Cowardice possesses the effeminate man; and the soul of the sluggard shall hunger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:16",
      "text": "He that keeps the commandment keeps his own soul; but he that despises his ways shall perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:17",
      "text": "He that has pity on the poor lends to the Lord; and he will recompense to him according to his gift.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:18",
      "text": "Chasten thy son, for so he shall be hopeful; and be not exalted in thy soul to haughtiness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:19",
      "text": "A malicious man shall be severely punished, and if he commit injury, he shall also lose his life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:20",
      "text": "Hear, son, the instruction of thy father, that thou mayest be wise at thy latter end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:21",
      "text": "There are many thoughts in a man's heart; but the counsel of the Lord abides for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:22",
      "text": "Mercy is a fruit to a man: and a poor man is better than a rich liar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:23",
      "text": "The fear of the Lord is life to a man: and he shall lodge without fear in places where knowledge is not seen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:24",
      "text": "He that unjustly hides his hands in his bosom, will not even bring them up to his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:25",
      "text": "When a pestilent character is scourged, a simple man is made wiser: and if thou reprove a wise man, he will understand discretion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:26",
      "text": "He that dishonours his father, and drives away his mother, shall be disgraced and shall be exposed to reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:27",
      "text": "A son who ceases to attend to the instruction of a father will cherish evil designs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:28",
      "text": "He that becomes surety for a foolish child will despise the ordinance: and the mouth of ungodly men shall drink down judgments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.19.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:29",
      "text": "Scourges are preparing for the intemperate, and punishments likewise for fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
